==============================================================================
1. Vivado Project Files
These are generated by the Vivado IDE and should not be tracked.
The main project file (.xpr) is kept for project setup, but intermediate
and build files are ignored.
==============================================================================
*.log
*.jou
*.wdb
*.hw
*.dir
*.str
*.tcl
*.sim
*.pb

Ignore Vivado's generated directories
hw/vivado/.runs/
hw/vivado/.hw/
hw/vivado/.ip_user_files/
hw/vivado/.srcs/
hw/vivado/*.cache/

==============================================================================
2. Arduino & Embedded Software
Arduino IDE-specific files and build outputs.
==============================================================================
sw/arduino/steganography_tester/.o
sw/arduino/steganography_tester/.elf
sw/arduino/steganography_tester/*.hex
sw/arduino/steganography_tester/build/

==============================================================================
3. Host Utility Files
Compiled binaries, build artifacts, and Python cache files.
==============================================================================
C++ decoder build artifacts
sw/utils/decoder/image_decoder
sw/utils/decoder/*.o

Python cache files
sw/utils/python_serial_bridge/pycache/
sw/utils/python_serial_bridge/*.pyc
==============================================================================
4. Data Files
Sample and encoded images. These can be large and are not part of the source code.
The data directory itself is tracked, but its contents are ignored.
==============================================================================
data/images/.bmp
data/images/.jpg
data/images/*.png

==============================================================================
5. Operating System Files
Files created by various operating systems.
==============================================================================
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
